ZH: 我在书店买了一个橡皮。
EN: I bought an eraser at the bookstore.
ZH: 这个橡皮很容易擦掉铅笔的痕迹。
EN: This eraser easily removes pencil marks.
ZH: 我的橡皮掉到地上了，我需要再买一个。
EN: My eraser fell on the ground, I need to buy another one.
ZH: 他用橡皮擦掉了错误的答案。
EN: He erased the wrong answer with an eraser.
ZH: 麦克在桌子上保持一支橡皮，以防他需要它。
EN: Mike keeps an eraser on his desk in case he needs it.
ZH: 这支橡皮是白色的。
EN: This eraser is white.
ZH: 我的橡皮已经用完了，需要买新的。
EN: My eraser is already used up, I need to buy a new one.
ZH: 这个橡皮水果味道很好闻。
EN: This eraser smells like fruit.
ZH: 她用橡皮抹去了桌子上的污渍。
EN: She erased the stains on the table with an eraser.
ZH: 我的铅笔开始变短，我需要用橡皮擦掉钢笔的笔迹。
EN: My pencil is getting shorter, I need to erase the pen marks with an eraser.
ZH: 橡皮很有弹性。
EN: The eraser is very flexible.
ZH: 我丢失了我的橡皮，你能借给我一支吗？
EN: I lost my eraser, can you lend me one?
ZH: 她在新铅笔上试验橡皮的效果。
EN: She is testing the effect of the eraser on a new pencil.
ZH: 这种橡皮可以消除纸上的墨汁。
EN: This type of eraser can eliminate ink on paper.
ZH: 我喜欢用大块橡皮，因为它们更容易握住。
EN: I prefer using large erasers because they are easier to grip.
ZH: 他的橡皮掉到地上后分成了两半。
EN: His eraser broke into two pieces after it fell on the ground.
ZH: 我现在有五支橡皮，我不需要再买了。
EN: I have five erasers now, I don't need to buy more.
ZH: 我的橡皮掉进了铅笔盒里。
EN: My eraser fell into the pencil case.
ZH: 她的橡皮很脏，需要清洗一下。
EN: Her eraser is dirty, it needs to be cleaned.
ZH: 他把橡皮擦碾碎后用到了别的用途上。
EN: He crushed the eraser and used it for something else.
